  • Constructor Details

    • Cell

      public Cell​(java.lang.String nomenclature, boolean hasMirror, char mirror, boolean isCorner, boolean isEdge, java.lang.String typeCorner, java.lang.String typeEdge, char isStart, char isEnd, boolean mirrorGuessed, boolean mirrorWrong)
      Name: Cell Constructor method of a cell.
      Parameters:
      nomenclature - - Cell nomenclature - nomenclature = String, nomenclature != null, nomenclature != ""
      hasMirror - - Attribute to determine if a cell has a mirror - hasMirror = boolean, hasMirror != null, hasMirror begins in false once the Cell object is created.
      mirror - - Mirror inclination - mirror = char, mirror != null, mirror begins empty once the Cell object is created.
      isCorner - - Attribute to determine if a cell is in a corner of the grid - isCorner = boolean, isCorner != null
      isEdge - - Attribute to determine if a cell is on an edge of the grid - isEdge = boolean, isEdge != null
      typeCorner - - Corner type if a cell is in a corner of the grid - typeCorner = String, typeCorner != null
      typeEdge - - Edge type if a cell is on an edge of the grid - typeEdge = String, typeEdge != null
      isStart - - Attribute to identify if a cell was chosen to begin a laser shot in it - isStart = char, isStart != null, isStart begins empty once the Cell object is created.
      isEnd - - Attribute to identify in which cell the laser beam ended its traversal - isEnd = char, isEnd != null, isEnd begins empty once the Cell object is created.
      mirrorGuessed - - Attribute to determine if a mirror present in a cell was guessed - mirrorGuessed = boolean, mirrorGuessed != null, mirrorGuessed begins in false once the Cell object is created.
      mirrorWrong - - Attribute to determine if a user guessed wrongly a mirror present in a cell - mirrorWrong = boolean, mirrorWrong != null, mirrorWrong begins in false once the Cell object is created.
